# Brand and voice

When writing or editing user-facing copy in this repository (marketing text, landing pages, release notes, security bulletins, in-product microcopy, or docs prose), follow the guidelines in `brand-guidelines/`:

- `brand-guidelines/brand.md` - brand attributes and anti-brand list.
- `brand-guidelines/voice-and-tone.md` - voice, tone by context, formatting.
- `brand-guidelines/lexicon.md` - product names, use/avoid words, forbidden patterns.

Defaults: be clear, precise, and calm; lead with the point; make concrete, verifiable claims. Avoid hype, fear-based security marketing, absolute security claims, unsourced numbers, and undefined jargon. Always spell the product "Mattermost."

This rule does not apply to code, identifiers, or test fixtures. To audit existing copy, run the `/content-review` skill.
